<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-26T22:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-26T22:34:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4387: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-27T12:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 8:44
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Chinese soldiers revolt against Chang Tso-lin evidently spreading
                            throughout railway zone, Legation informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>